    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a superlative example of naturally aspirated precision. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a razor-sharp 8,000 RPM redline. The Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox offers short, mechanical throws, paired with a variable M differential lock for optimal corner-exit traction. This specimen is mechanically flawless: the subframe has been reinforced, the VANOS system has been professionally bulletproofed, and the rod bearings have been replaced as preventative maintenance. The exterior retains its factory depth with zero swirl marks, while the interior features pristine Nappa leather and an Alcantara-wrapped steering wheel. With a suspension geometry refreshed by polyurethane bushings and Bilstein dampers, this M3 provides the telepathic feedback and chassis rigidity expected of a concours-level collector car.",
